The secret of the glow over Norway unsealed: Russians test missile
A special light effect of unknown origin could be observed over Norway.
The Russian Defense Ministry only yesterday admitted that it had tested an intercontinental ballistic missile near the Norwegian border.
But the launch was again unsuccessful, and the missile, referred to as the "Bulava" missile, which was originally intended to be the pride of the Russian army, is slowly becoming a black moth for both Russian generals and Prime Minister Vladimir Putin.
Even its repeated presence in missile tests did not have an appropriate effect on the success of test flights.
