Gradual calming
As enshined in the country's constitution in 1978, China's one-child policy is probably the most controversial mandate introduced under communist rule to date.
Couples who violated politics faced huge fines -- up to three times their annual salary in some areas -- and discrimination at work.
Chinese officials pushed for a policy that helped the country prevent critical use of natural resources, while human rights advocates were condemned in pursuing the policy.
