He hopes the new service will eventually connect Britain with an international network of fast, reliable trains and connect the great agglomerations of Midland, the North and Scotland with London.
Neglected stagnant waters should reduce passenger and commercial transport times, and the transition from aircraft and cars to rail could reduce carbon emissions and eliminate congestion on the roads.
