High Speed Two (HS2), a company set up in January to provide the government with a viable study, submitted its report to Lord Adonis on December 30, the Times reported.
It provided him with a detailed map of the routes of the next planned stage of the high-speed network.
A new route to London's connection to the West Midlands has been proposed within five metres in urban areas and boroughs where the impact of life could be problematic.
In the open countryside, a final route was planned for 25 m.
HS2 also foresees three options for a large high-speed network leading north.
Lord Adonis will answer in the spring.
