In a speech from Oslo: a "just war," Obama earned praise from the right.
On Friday, the American right welcomed a speech Barack Obama gave the day before in Oslo, satisfied that the 2009 Nobel Peace Prize winner was advocating the concept of a "just war" against America's enemies.
Conservatives who initially deeded Obama on October 9 applauded the president's speech, including Sarah Palin, the former vice presidential candidate in the 2008 election.
